# CLAUDE.md

Project-level instructions for Claude Code. Copy this file to the project root, replace `<...>` placeholders, and tune the rules to your codebase.

## Project

- Name: `<project name>`
- Description: `<one line>`
- Stack: `<React + TypeScript + Tailwind + ...>`
- Design system reference: `DESIGN.md`
- Token files: `styles/primitives.css`, `styles/semantic.css`

## Available Agents

This project uses the `fairmind-design` plugin. Available agents:

- `fairmind-design-verification` — design-to-code parity check against Figma
- `fairmind-token-analyzer` — semantic token usage and drift detection
- `fairmind-component-composition-reviewer` — composite-component structure review
- `fairmind-figma-code-connect-generator` — Figma Code Connect maintenance
- `fairmind-accessibility-orchestrator` — full a11y audit (orchestrator)
- `fairmind-wcag-compliance-auditor` — WCAG 2.1 AA conformance
- `fairmind-color-contrast-specialist` — contrast against WCAG 1.4.3 / 1.4.11
- `fairmind-keyboard-navigation-tester` — keyboard operability
- `fairmind-screen-reader-tester` — screen reader comprehension
- `fairmind-claude-md-compliance-checker` — CLAUDE.md conformance (mandatory closing step)

## Available Commands

- `/design-verify <component-path> <figma-url>` — full design quality gate
- `/a11y-audit <component-path-or-url>` — full accessibility audit
- `/code-connect <component-path> <figma-url>` — Code Connect generation/update
- `/design-task-close` — mandatory closing compliance check

## Quality Gates

| Change kind | Mandatory agents |
|---|---|
| New or modified component | `fairmind-design-verification`, `fairmind-token-analyzer`, `fairmind-component-composition-reviewer` |
| Component touching color | + `fairmind-color-contrast-specialist` |
| Component with interactivity | + `fairmind-keyboard-navigation-tester`, `fairmind-screen-reader-tester` |
| Page-level change | `fairmind-accessibility-orchestrator` |
| Any task close | `fairmind-claude-md-compliance-checker` (always) |

## Cannot Proceed If

- Any mandatory agent returned `FAIL` and was not re-run after a fix
- Any hardcoded hex color exists in code outside `styles/primitives.css`
- Any interactive element lacks an accessible name
- Any focusable element lacks a visible focus indicator
- Build, lint, or tests fail
- `fairmind-claude-md-compliance-checker` returned `BLOCKED`

## If An Agent Fails

1. Read the agent's report.
2. Apply the recommended fixes in the affected files.
3. Re-run the failing agent on the fixed files.
4. Continue only when the agent returns `PASS`.

## Anti-patterns (auto-grep)

The compliance checker will fail the task if any of the following appear in modified files:

- Inline hex colors: regex `#[0-9a-fA-F]{3,8}` (outside `styles/primitives.css`)
- Tailwind arbitrary values: `text-\[`, `bg-\[`, `p-\[`, `m-\[`
- `<div ... onClick`
- `<a href="#"`
- `outline:\s*none` without a paired `:focus-visible` rule

## Build, Lint, Test

- Build: `<npm run build>`
- Lint: `<npm run lint>`
- Type check: `<npm run typecheck>`
- Test: `<npm test>`
- Storybook (if used): `<npm run storybook>`

A task is not complete until all four commands above exit `0`.

## Design System

- Token policy: components reference semantic tokens only. See the `design-token-conventions` skill in `fairmind-design`.
- New semantic tokens require a DS proposal documented in `DESIGN.md`.
- Sub-folder rules: see `styles/CLAUDE.md` and `src/components/CLAUDE.md` (create as needed).
